explanation:
A) Union membership has fallen in the last 50 years. Reasons include the shift
from manufacturing to service jobs, and new legislation (such as occupational safety laws)
provides the sorts of protections that workers could once only obtain from their unions.

B) Voluntary (or permissible) bargaining items are neither mandatory nor illegal;
they become a part of negotiations only through the joint agreement of both management and
union. Neither party can compel the other to negotiate over voluntary items.
